        public static javaslang.control.Validation<String,Cron> build(javaslang.collection.Set<Integer> minutes,
                                                              javaslang.collection.Set<Integer> hours,
                                                              javaslang.collection.Set<Integer> daysOfMonth,
                                                              javaslang.collection.Set<Month> months,
                                                              javaslang.collection.Set<DayOfWeek> daysOfWeek)
        Programmatically reate a Cron specification.
        Parameters:
        minutes - minutes of the hour (0-59)
        hours - hours of the day (0-23)
        daysOfMonth - the days of the month (1-31). To specify the last day of the month, use DayOfMonthSpec.LAST_DAY_OF_MONTH
        months - months of the year
        daysOfWeek - the days of the week
        Returns:
        a Cron object or an error message

      • isMatch

        public boolean isMatch(ZonedDateTime dateTime)
        Will return true if the date time given is a match for this cron specification (in other words if execution would trigger at that exact date and time). Note that it will return true only if given the exact date and time, with the second and millisecond both set to 0.
        Parameters:
        dateTime - the date time to test
        Returns:
        true if the cron would execute at that dateTime
        See Also:
        CronExecution.gapToClosestExecution(com.github.emmanueltouzery.crony.Cron, java.time.ZonedDateTime)
